               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾāmmǝra Māryām “Miracles of Mary" (fols. 3ra-72va)&#xD; I-1) Maṣḥafa
                     śǝrʿāt, Introductory rite of al-Muʿallaqah and hymns (fol. 3ra-7rb)&#xD; I-2)
                     Introductory exhortation (fols. 7va-8vb)&#xD; I-3) ʾƎsaggǝd laki wa-ʾǝweddǝsaki
                     ... “I worship Thee ...” (fols. 8vb-9vb)&#xD; I-4) Taʾāmmǝra Māryām “Miracles of
                     Mary”: 66 miracles (fols. 10ra-72va)&#xD; I-5) ʾAkkonu bǝʾsi... “Does not the
                     man... ” (distributed among the miracles of Mary, fols. 12rb-18rb,
                     66rb-68va)&#xD; II) Taʾāmmǝra Mikāʾel “Miracles of Michael”: 5 miracles (fols.
                     72vb-76rb)&#xD; III) Taʾāmmǝra ʾIyasus “Miracles of Jesus”: 5 miracles (fols.
                     76va-80vb)&#xD; &#xD; Additiones 1-5.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The miracles of St Mary (Text I-4) are partly numbered (erroneously). The
                        1st miracle is followed by a hymn:</note>
                     <note>- Sobä ṣäḥafä Däqsǝyos täʾamriha ʾǝludä ... "When Däqsǝyos wrote the
                        collection of her miracles ..." (<locus target="#11va">11va</locus>).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>The miracles of Michael (Text II) are followed by ʿarke-hymns.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
